-- Syria Names Ghalawanji as Interim Premier After Hijab Dismissal
-- B y   N a y l a   R a z z o u k
-- 2012-08-06T09:30:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-06/syria-names-ghalawanji-as-interim-premier-after-hijab-dismissal.html
Syria  appointed Oman Ghalawanji as
interim prime minister after Riad Hijab was dismissed less than
two months at the position, state-run Syrian TV reported.  Ghalawanji is deputy prime minister for services affairs
and minister of local administration, according to Syrian Arab
 News Agency .  The news agency reported on June 23 that President Bashar
al-Assad, battling civil unrest and calls for his removal from
office, appointed Hijab, a former agriculture minister, as prime
minister.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nayla Razzouk in Dubai at 
